topic: Movie Workflow Series ("Tv series Without a Trace explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for television series
goals.2: Return the number of seasons and episodes per season of the tv series (the result set must be triples of season IRI, label and #episodes).
goals.3: Get the number of episodes in which the cast members played a role. Who are the most present actors? (the result set must be a list of triples actor/actress IRI, label and #episodes)
goals.4: Check who is the actor who acted in more films while working on "Without a Trace" (the result set must be a list of triples actor/actress IRI, label and #films).
goals.5: Compare Without a Trace with the tv series "Cold Case" in terms of number of seasons, episods and cast members (the result set must be two elements -one for each tv series- of tv series IRI, label, #seasons, #episodes and #cast members).
goals.6: Return the actors who are members of the cast of Without a Trace have [Kavin Bacon number](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Degrees_of_Kevin_Bacon#:~:text=Kevin%20Bacon%20himself%20has%20a,Bacon%20number%20is%20N%2B1.) equal to 2 (the result set must be a list of couples actor/actress IRI and label).
goals.7: Consider the actors who are members of the cast of Cold Case. Amongst the tv series which these actors acted return only those which received more than 2 awards (the result set must be triples of tv series IRI, label, #awards won).

name: workflow2_3

1.narrative:
startup the evaluation
setup the file and create the empty json
literal properties of Without a Trace
single literal associated to an URI
1.query: SELECT ?tv_series ?name ?numEpisodes ?numSeasons WHERE { VALUES ?tv_series { wd:Q826477 wd:Q733960 } ?tv_series wdt:P1113 ?numEpisodes ; wdt:P2437 ?numSeasons . ?tv_series sc:name ?name } GROUP BY ?tv_series ?name

2.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 1 in the file
find seasons and episodes
find object properties of Without a Trace
output: original language of film or TV show
original language of film or TV show

2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?part ?partName ?numEpisodes WHERE { wd:Q826477 wdt:P527 ?part . ?part wdt:P1113 ?numEpisodes. ?part <http://schema.org/name> ?partName . }

SELECT ?actor ?actorName COUNT(DISTINCT ?episode) AS ?numEpisodes WHERE { wd:Q733960 wdt:P527{2} ?episode . ?episode wdt:P161 ?actor . ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . } GROUP BY ?actor ?actorName ORDER BY DESC(?numEpisodes) LIMIT 10

SELECT ?tv_series ?name (COUNT(DISTINCT ?actor) AS ?numActors) WHERE { VALUES ?tv_series { wd:Q826477 wd:Q733960 } ?tv_series wdt:P527{2} ?episode . ?episode wdt:P161 ?actor . ?tv_series <http://schema.org/name> ?name . } GROUP BY ?tv_series ?name

3.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
episodes of the first season
output: Are You Now Or Have You Ever Been?

3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pName ?o ?oName WHERE { wd:Q39069555 ?p ?o. ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pName . ?o <http://schema.org/name> ?oName . } ORDER BY ?pName
output: original language of film or TV show

3.narrative: count the presence of the actors in the Tv serie
3.query: SELECT ?actor ?actorName COUNT(DISTINCT ?episode) AS ?numEpisodes WHERE { wd:Q826477 wdt:P527/wdt:P527 ?episode . ?episode wdt:P161 ?actor . ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . } GROUP BY ?actor ?actorName ORDER BY DESC(?numEpisodes) LIMIT 6

4.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
start and end
see properties and objects of Anthony LaPaglia
output: Tony Award for Best Actor in a Play
Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series

4.query: SELECT ?s ?sName ?p ?pName WHERE { ?s ?p wd:Q308124 . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pName . ?s <http://schema.org/name> ?sName . } ORDER BY ?pName LIMIT 20
SELECT DISTINCT ?class ?className WHERE { ?s wdt:P161 wd:Q308124 ; wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }
SELECT ?film ?filmName WHERE { ?film wdt:P161 wd:Q308124 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q11424 . ?film <http://schema.org/name> ?filmName . } ORDER BY ?filmName
output: So I Married an Axe Murderer

4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pName WHERE { ?film wdt:P161 wd:Q308124 ; ?p ?o; wdt:P31 wd:Q11424 . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pName . FILTER(REGEX(?pName, "date")) }

SELECT ?actor ?actorName COUNT(DISTINCT ?film) AS ?numFilms WHERE { ?season wdt:P179 wd:Q826477 . ?season wdt:P527 ?episode . ?episode wdt:P161 ?actor. wd:Q826477 wdt:P580 ?startTime ; wdt:P582 ?endTime . ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424 ; wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P577 ?publicationDate . ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . FILTER (?publicationDate > ?startTime AND ?publicationDate < ?endTime ) } GROUP BY ?actor ?actorName ORDER BY DESC(?numFilms) LIMIT 10

6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?person ?personName ?personSurname WHERE { ?person wdt:P734 ?surname . ?person <http://schema.org/name> ?personName . ?surname <http://schema.org/name> ?personSurname . FILTER EXISTS{ ?film wdt:P31 wd:Q11424 ; wdt:P161 ?person . } FILTER(REGEX(?personSurname, "Bacon")) } LIMIT 10

SELECT ?actor ?actorName ?film ?filmName WHERE { wd:Q826477 wdt:P161 ?actor . ?film wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . ?film <http://schema.org/name> ?filmName . }

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ?actor) WHERE { wd:Q826477 wdt:P161 ?actor . ?filmMiddle wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle . ?film wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . FILTER NOT EXISTS{ ?film3 wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . } ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . }

SELECT DISTINCT ?actor ?actorName WHERE { wd:Q826477 wdt:P161 ?actor . ?filmMiddle wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle . ?film wdt:P161 ?actorMiddle ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . FILTER NOT EXISTS{ ?film3 wdt:P161 ?actor ; wdt:P161 wd:Q3454165 . } ?actor <http://schema.org/name> ?actorName . } LIMIT 30

7.query: SELECT ?s ?name COUNT( ?aw) AS ?awards WHERE { { SELECT DISTINCT ?s WHERE{ wd:Q733960 wdt:P527{2} ?episode . ?episode wdt:P161 ?actor . ?s wdt:P161 ?actor . } } ?s wdt:P166 ?aw; wdt:P31 wd:Q5398426 . ?s sc:name ?name . } GROUP BY ?s ?name HAVING (COUNT( ?aw)>2) ORDER BY DESC(?awards)
